So Livejournal says I haven't updated in 30 weeks. But like it really matters? No one reads this anyway. Which is probably for the best because this is supposed to be a journal. What if I wanted to put my private thoughts into this blank little box?

So I found a blank notebook, you know, the spiral ones that are used in school. And I decided to just... start writing in it. Unintentionally, I've started this thing called Thoughts of a Mind. I keep the notebook at my desk, and when I think of something, I write it down.
Of course I don't write down EVERYTHING. Just things I want to.

It's actually turned out to be a cool idea. It's interesting to look back and see what I've written. And it helps, kind of, organize all the millions of thoughts that are running to and fro about my mind.

So there's been this rising tension of sorts for awhile now. It started when I lost my best friend over something stupid. But we had just failed to communicate properly with each other. It had to be over. All things come to an end someday.
Now that she's gone... it's left me this sinking, empty feeling in the pit of my stomach. I'm not sure it's because I miss HER, I think it's because I miss my BEST FRIEND. This will sound rather stupid... but I've realized that I am no one's "Number One" on myspace. God, I feel so lame saying that. But I can't deny the fact that it's unsettling. It makes me feel as if no one NEEDS me. Sure, people may want to have me as a friend. But if it came down to it and all my friends had to choose who they would pick if they absolutely had to? It wouldn't be me. 

Very unsettling.
Very empty.
Very lonely.

So my first entry in... maybe over half a year, has been depressing.
Great way to start off this blogging business again!

You know this must be good when I haven't updated in like over a year.




Keith Richards. Singapore. Elizabeth and her hardcore outfit thing. Whoa.

I haven't once updated on my trip to Greece. Well, it was amazing. To be honest I don't feel like going into full detail. But when I was in a hotel, I found a little black book, lying on the desk carelessly. I opened it, and this is what I found. The sun was going up and I was walking towards the Acropolis. My mouth could not utter a word. As I walked I felt the motion of the stones beneath my feet. I stared in admiration. I saw visions... that my mind could not fathom. They were enormous... and compassion became my guide to comprehension. People from another era... placed stone upon stone for a sculpting dream to occur... feeling... worn out, dipping into the goddess' heart, I enter the Parthenon. Floated all around... she pushed me away. I had not understood, and nor had she. And of course I was arrogant. It took me days... months... years... to realize the essence of this land I tread upon. What vibrations it keeps inside, the joys and the sorrows. I realized that... She, Herself, was the one to allow me to partake in Her secrets... What should I scent? What should I respect? What should I touch? What should I hide? What should I disclose. I smelt the earth, I watched the clear blue sky, I smelt!!! the earth's heartbeats, I heard the waves from Piraeus and I was entwined by her threads, daily. They held me tight... then they would let me go Until one Morning in May... a Sunday, it must have been, Walking among her, With you on my mind... muttering a song... Fly me to the moon and let me sing among the stars... The vision reached my soul Athens, Athens, Athena! She is a woman! A full-blooded female. She is uncontrollable, She grumbles... She's desirable, unrestrained. A maniac... Difficult, unapproachable, witty, unexpected. She acts out. She's rude, passionate, abrupt... as she Transforms herself into shapes of adoration. She can as light as a feather... Or she can burden your soul like iron. She may seem strong, yet her heart can break with each instance that goes by. It is her ego, I think, that keeps her intact. Yes, she has her ups and downs... she's intense. She has bouts of laughter... she has curves... Her gaze is powerful and she calls upon those She desires. When she wants to. She has the aura of a witch... I couldn't even begin to tell you!! But I can help you find your way. That she may never deny you... Yes!!! There is one... as long as you have Kindness. Love and Persistency. Relax with me, boil some herbal tea, louisa , It will calm down the parts that I require, And add to the cup a drop of liquor. You must look Athens in the eyes. Be honest with your thoughts. Share them kindly... these things fatigue. Open your arms, and the city will come to you. I promise you that. I know her. She has taught me well. You'll adore her forever... no matter how ephemeral "forever" may be, It is true, because it it momentary. Remember, "Forever" means "This very moment..." Find it.

"We have lost our spiritual equilibrium and reversed our values.
We have exploited the poor and called it the lottery.
We have rewarded laziness and called it welfare.
We have killed our unborn and called it choice.
We have shot abortionists and called it justifiable.
We have neglected to discipline our children and called it building self-esteem.
We have abused power and called it politics.
We have coveted our neighbor's possessions and called it ambition.
We have polluted the air with profanity and pornography and called it
freedom of expression.
We have ridiculed the time-honored values of our forefathers and called it
enlightenment."

[mood| i dunno] [music|Between the Bars- Elliot Smith ] so yeah, i think i'm going to do some venting of my own. if anyone cares to listen. and i'm too lazy for caps lock. well today i'm doing nothing, as usual. i seriously have no social life. and i know it's my fault. i mean i don't call anyone, ask if people want to come over. and i don't know why i do that. sometimes i just don't want to be around anyone. i'm like this outsider. and i feel like i have no real friends. you know, those ones that you're attached on the hip to and are always with them. so i guess i'm feeling a little insecure. and lately, i've think i've been TOO nice. i mean i'm always going out of my way to give someone something, and do things for people. do you think it's because i want attention? that just sounds sooo mean, because i love helping people. really, i do. but i never get ANYTHING in return. never. no one goes out their way for me, or ever tells me nice things. yeah, insecure. i just don't feel extremely loved right now, so i'm a little lost. hopefully this will pass soon. maybe it's the weather. not venting, more like fucking complaining.

This isn't mine, I got it off something from Elizabethtown but fuck, it totally describes me. Well, mostly. There are lost hours. The ones nobody thinks about. The one where everybody is asleep - and the world is cool and quiet. Those are the hours that are completely mine. Completely, absolutely mine. Whether to sit in the quiet, listening to the crickets with their back and forth chirping, sit at a counter, thinking and drinking black coffee or driving on a highway with a sky darker blue than pillow cut sapphires. In those moments, it's all yours - and everything you love matters. Everything. The ultimate luxury, even if it's only every now and again. .... Wow. I just died a little. But in a good way. No, that does not contradict itself.. shut up. Only thing I would add would be sitting on the computer all fucking night.
